<item>
            <title>[SOLR-509] Event Listeners called before request handlers are informed of SolrCore</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-509</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Nullpointer-when-using-QuerySenderListener-to16201207.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Nullpointer-when-using-QuerySenderListener-to16201207.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thijs noticed NullPointerException from SearchHandler on startup when trying to configure some firstSearcher events using QuerySenderListener.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is the events are getting triggered as soon as the firstSearcher is opened, but the SOlrCore isn&apos;t finished being initialized, so inform(SolrCore) hasn&apos;t been called on all the Handlers (and some handlers aren&apos;t fully initialized and ready to process requests yet.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;We need to more the firstSearcher event handling after inform has been called on all SolrCoreAware objects.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12392121">SOLR-509</key>
